## What is Squadron?

Squadron is an autonomous development system built on the [GitHub Copilot SDK](https://www.npmjs.com/package/github-copilot-sdk). It listens for GitHub webhooks, triages issues with a **PM agent**, spawns specialized **dev and review agents** to do the work, and coordinates the entire lifecycle ‚Äî from issue to merged PR ‚Äî without human intervention.

Each agent runs in its own Copilot SDK session with its own git worktree, tools, and context. The PM agent delegates work using the SDK's native **subagent** and **custom agent** primitives. Everything is configurable via YAML.

### Key Features

- **Multi-agent orchestration** ‚Äî PM, feature dev, bug fix, PR review, security review agents
- **Copilot SDK native** ‚Äî uses `CustomAgentConfig`, subagents, MCP servers, skills
- **GitHub-native** ‚Äî GitHub App webhooks, issue/PR CRUD, label taxonomy, approval flows
- **Branch isolation** ‚Äî each agent gets its own git worktree
- **Dependency tracking** ‚Äî agents can block on other issues with BFS cycle detection
- **Circuit breakers** ‚Äî per-role limits on tool calls, turns, and active duration
- **Sleep/wake lifecycle** ‚Äî agents sleep when blocked, wake when blockers resolve
- **Reconciliation loop** ‚Äî detects stuck agents and auto-escalates
- **BYOK support** ‚Äî bring your own API key (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) or use Copilot auth

